            },
            "description": "Planning session is one of the main ceremony of scrum methodology. Developers gather around and try to estimate the features they want to develop in the next sprint as product owner defines their priorities. but sometimes its forgotten that this estimate number provided by developer is not an simple number, as it is more of nominal number of a distributed number. Refined Planning Poker solves this by using Robert C. Martin\u2019s formula on estimation. Each Estimation is completed with three numbers, one for the Best case, one for normal case, and another for the worst case. The result is a nominal number plus standard deviation which can inform developers and product owner how much more or less the development may take long. ",
